  <h3>Filtering Resources</h3> 
  <p>When using a console, a common use case is when the user must select from resources (e.g. pages, components, assets, etc.). This can take the form of a list for example from which the author must choose an item.</p> 
  <p>In order to keep the list to a reasonable size and also relevant to the use case, a filter can be implemented in the form of a custom predicate. See <a href="../../../sites/developing/using/customizing-page-authoring-touch.md#main-pars-title-936239831">this article</a> for details.</p> 
